<HEADLINE>
<P>
MALCOLM X 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I am white. For a long time my color has hampered me from voicing my opinion of 
Malcolm X. 
</P>
<P>
I have never been against his teachings. 
</P>
<P>
On the contrary, I believe that his views of black suppression and how to 
remedy the situation are just. 
</P>
<P>
Thank you, Charisse Jones, for the clear and precise article "The Rebirth of 
Malcolm X." I hope that my white contemporaries have taken the time to read it 
in full, instead of banishing it to the wastepaper basket -- as has been done 
many times before with anything that has contradicted popular white beliefs. 
</P>
<P>
MONICA BLUMENTHAL 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
