COLLEGE NEWS: PRESIDENT'S AWARD AT GRADUATE SCHOOL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Claremont Graduate School has established the President's Award for the Visual 
Arts to be given annually to a graduating master of fine arts student. 
</P>
<P>
Under the program, the school will acquire a work from the artist for $1,000 
and exhibit it on the campus for one year. 
</P>
