<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE NEWS: CITRUS COLLEGE STUDENTS TAKE FORENSICS HONORS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Three Citrus College speech students have won top honors in a forensics 
competition held at Pasadena City College. 
</P>
<P>
Shana Furlow won first place in dramatic interpretation, and Laura Chiara and 
Ted Torres won second place in duo interpretation. 
</P>
<P>
The competition drew students from 50 colleges and universities. Citrus is 
located in Glendora. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
