<TEXT>
<P>
. . . Lennie Del Genio, the Las Vegas bookie whose uninformed Oscar odds are 
routinely reported as entertainment news, was heard in a recent radio interview 
picking Brenda Fritcher (it's Fricker) to win best supporting actress, and 
Oliver Sloan (it's Stone) to win the best director award over "My Left Foot's" 
John (it's Jim) Sheridan. 
</P>
