<HEADLINE>
<P>
BY THE SEA, BY THE SEA; 
</P>
<P>
FOR SOME OF L.A.'S BEST AIR AND BEST FOOD, TRY SANTA MONICA. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Kathie Jenkins 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Chinois on Main, 2709 Main St. (213) 392-9025. Style: Wolfgang Puck's other 
restaurant, this one with a French/Asian twist. Setting: Atomic elan. 
</P>
<P>
Recommended: Sauteed foie gras with pineapple; whole catfish with ginger; creme 
brulee. Cost per person: $35-$50. 
</P>
<P>
DC 3, at the Santa Monica Airport, 2800 Donald Douglas Loop N. (213) 399-2323. 
Style: Takeoff on grill food. Setting: Nucleus '90. Recommended: Rack of lamb; 
charred tuna; sea bass in saffron broth. Cost per person: $22-$50. 
</P>
<P>
Michael's, 1147 3rd St. (213) 451-0843. Style: Same arty mood and fancy food -- 
slightly lower prices. Setting: Gorgeous garden; good art. Recommended: Saddle 
of lamb; chicken with duck liver and morels. Cost per person: $40-$60. 
</P>
<P>
Opera On Ocean, 1551 Ocean Ave. (213) 393-9224. Style: Casually elegant 
Mediterranean. Setting: Beach chic. Recommended: Walnut olive bread; whole 
spiced marinated fish; grilled lavender chicken. Cost per person: $20-$45. 
</P>
<P>
Valentino, 3115 Pico Blvd. (213) 829-4313. Style: Haute Italian served in haute 
splendor. Setting: Modern palazzo-esque. Recommended: Warm lobster salad; 
calamaretti, fried baby squid; veal shanks. Cost per person: $40-$60. Kathie 
Jenkins 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Drawing, , TED ENGELBART 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
