<HEADLINE>
<P>
DUCHESS OF YORK AT REST AFTER BIRTH OF SECOND DAUGHTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LONDON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Duchess of York rested inside a maternity hospital Saturday, a day after 
giving birth to her second daughter, the sixth in line to the British throne. 
</P>
<P>
The 7-pound, 1 1/2-ounce girl was delivered by Cesarean section Friday evening 
in the presence of her father, Prince Andrew, Buckingham Palace said. The baby 
was in a breech position. 
</P>
<P>
Saturday, crowds of photographers and well-wishers remained on a vigil outside 
to catch a glimpse of the baby, the second child for the 30-year-old duchess, 
the former Sarah Ferguson, and Prince Andrew. 
</P>
<P>
No name was announced for the newborn princess. 
</P>
