</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
DELAWARE RIVER FOULED BY ACCIDENTAL OIL SPILL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MARCUS HOOK, Pa. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A tanker on Friday spilled about 1,000 gallons of oil into the Delaware River, 
the Coast Guard said. 
</P>
<P>
Unloading was stopped and floating booms were placed in the water around the 
ship. A private anti-pollution contractor also was called in to clean up the 
spill. 
</P>
