NATION IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
ILLINOIS; 
</P>
<P>
SPY COMPARES CRIME TO INSIDER TRADING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and Wire reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
John A. Walker Jr., jailed for life for masterminding a family spy ring, said 
his crimes were no worse than insider trading on the stock market. 
</P>
<P>
In an interview with CBS' "60 Minutes," to be broadcast today, the former Navy 
