<BYLINE>
<P>
By MAL FLORENCE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
USC nose tackle Don Gibson suffered a broken left ankle Saturday in a game-type 
spring practice scrimmage at the Coliseum. 
</P>
<P>
Gibson played only in the Rose Bowl game against Michigan after being sidelined 
during the regular season while recuperating from surgery on his left knee. 
</P>
<P>
