<HEADLINE>
<P>
DRIVE-BY SHOOTING LEAVES 3 WOUNDED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Three men were wounded in a drive-by shooting early Saturday morning as they 
walked with a friend in Southeast San Diego. 
</P>
<P>
Police said that the men exchanged words with the passengers of a passing 
compact car in the 1000 block of 43rd Street about 2 a.m. Then, according to a 
witness, the driver of the car made a U-turn and shots rang out as it passed 
the group on the sidewalk. 
</P>
<P>
One of the men was hit in the groin, another in the arm and the third in the 
leg. None of the wounds was life-threatening, police said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
