<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAN ARRESTED IN WIFE'S DEATH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Police arrested a Hawthorne man Saturday in connection with the stabbing death 
of his common-law wife. 
</P>
<P>
Leonard Binns, 38, was being held without bail after police found Rose Ann 
Thompson, 29 in their apartment at 4080 120th St. with multiple stab wounds 
shortly after 7 a.m. Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
She was pronounced dead on arrival at Robert F. Kennedy Medical Center in 
Hawthorne, a Sheriff's Department spokesman said. The spokesman declined to 
give further details. 
</P>
</TEXT>
