<P>
BODY OF MAN FOUND FOLLOWING FIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An early morning fire in Pacific Beach was quickly extinguished by San Diego 
firefighters Saturday, who then discovered the body of a middle-aged man in the 
gutted apartment. 
</P>
<P>
A county coroner's office spokesman said that the man, estimated at between 30 
and 50 years of age, had not been identified late Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
San Diego Fire Department arson investigators are looking into the cause of the 
fire at 2303 Grand Ave. 
</P>
