<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGH SCHOOL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
ZINNER WINS TWO GAMES, STRIKES OUT 21 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Alicia Zinner struck out 11 and held Fountain Valley to one hit -- a bunt 
single -- and teammate Phronsie Franco hit a solo home run to lift Thousand 
Oaks to a 1-0 softball victory Saturday in a Tournament of Champions 
championship semifinal game at Peralta Park in Anaheim. 
</P>
<P>
A right-handed senior, Zinner struck out 10 and scattered five hits earlier in 
the day, pacing the Lancers (8-3) to a 4-3 victory over Los Alamitos. Franco 
also homered in that game. 
</P>
<P>
Thousand Oaks' Amy Chellevold had four hits and two RBIs for the day. 
</P>
<P>
In other softball games: 
</P>
<P>
Hart 3-3, Notre Dame 0-4 -- Kym Weil took a win and a loss as Hart split a 
nonleague doubleheader. 
</P>
<P>
Simona Errico led off the fifth inning of the second game with a single and 
scored on Darcy Anderson's single to give visiting Notre Dame a 4-0 lead. Hart 
rallied for three runs in the bottom of the inning, but Notre Dame starter 
Becca Berline (4-3) held on to earn the victory after losing the first game, 
despite striking out eight. 
</P>
<P>
Weil (6-2) took the loss in relief for Hart (7-2). Notre Dame is 4-3. 
</P>
<P>
In the first game, Hart's Weil, a senior right-hander, struck out 12, walked 
two and allowed two hits in shutting out Notre Dame. 
</P>
<P>
Palmdale 4, Paraclete 1 -- A victory in the Palmdale tournament gave the host 
team (12-3) its second tournament championship in two weeks. 
</P>
<P>
Senior right-hander Angie LePage (10-2) won her second game of the day and 
allowed only four hits while striking out four. LePage defeated Alemany 
earlier, 5-1. 
</P>
<P>
Alemany 5, Quartz Hill 0 -- Melanie Howard, a senior right-hander, limited 
Quartz Hill (6-4) to three hits as Alemany (9-3) finished third in the 10-team 
Palmdale tournament. 
</P>
<P>
Paraclete 7, Quartz Hill 0 -- Laura Staats had three RBI for Paraclete in a 
semifinal game of the Palmdale tournament. Paraclete's Shannon Peterson struck 
out six and yielded three hits. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
BASEBALL 
</P>
<P>
Millikan 7, Alemany 1 -- The Indians were held to six hits, losing their second 
game in two days, in a second-round Redondo-Palos Verdes tournament game at 
Millikan. 
</P>
<P>
Leo Tejada had two hits for Alemany (5-6), and Scott Goldsmith scored the 
Indians' lone run on an error in the third. 
</P>
<P>
In other baseball games: 
</P>
<P>
Highland Hall 11, Mesrobian 1 -- In addition to pitching a three-hitter and 
striking out nine, Robert Ramirez (4-1) picked up three hits and drove in two 
runs in a non-league game at North Valley Colt field. 
</P>
<P>
Shortstop Tommy Tominaga had three hits, including a double and a triple, and 
five RBIs for the Hawks (7-1). 
</P>
<P>
Palos Verdes 8, Crespi 1 -- The Celts stranded seven runners and were held to 
four hits in the second round of the Redondo-Palos Verdes tournament at Redondo 
Union High. 
</P>
<P>
Crespi (6-3-1) scored its lone run on Rick Marino's sacrifice fly. 
</P>
<P>
Calabasas 5-6, L.A. Baptist 4-5 -- Calabasas extended itself to the final out 
of each game, the second going to eight innings, in sweeping visiting L. A. 
Baptist. 
</P>
<P>
In the first game, Calabasas made a winner of Greg Wimmer (2-0) when Pat 
Schaffer hit a bases-loaded single with two out in the bottom of the seventh. 
Wimmer pitched two innings of relief and struck out four. 
</P>
<P>
Steve Klein took the loss for L. A. Baptist. 
</P>
<P>
Klein (0-3) also was the loser in the second game, when he walked Sam Voita 
with the bases loaded and two out in the bottom of the eighth. Schaffer (1-1) 
earned the win in relief. 
</P>
<P>
Channel Islands 7-3, Santa Paula 0-1 -- Jim Padilla struck out three and walked 
none in pitching a two-hitter for Channel Islands (9-3) in the first game. 
Channel Islands' Jacob Cruz had a 19-game hitting streak snapped in the second 
game. 
</P>
<P>
Montclair Prep 16-7, Chaminade 5-14 -- Left-hander Greg Galloway (2-0) threw a 
complete game and Justin Stark led Chaminade (7-2-1) with six RBIs in the 
second game of a doubleheader. Brent Polacheck homered in both games and had a 
total of 9 RBIs for visiting Montclair Prep (6-2). 
</P>
</TEXT>
