<HEADLINE>
<P>
HOME BUYERS FAIRS TO FEATURE LOAN EXPERTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Figuring out the mortgage market is one of the most confusing steps in buying a 
home. At the Los Angeles Times Home Buyers Fairs, you can get help from home 
loan experts: 
</P>
<P>
 -- Major lenders will offer free pre-qualifying for home loans, tell you how 
much house you can afford and give tips on new mortgages. 
</P>
<P>
Free consumer guides will be available. 
</P>
<P>
 -- Representatives from the state Housing Financy Agency will explain Gov. 
George Deukmejian's new first-time buyer program, and FHA and VA officials will 
explain their loan programs. 
</P>
<P>
The all-day Home Buyers Fairs will be held May 12 at the Los Angeles County 
Fairgrounds in Pomona; May 19 at the Woodland Hills Marriott Hotel in the San 
Fernando Valley and May 26 at the Anaheim Convention Center in Orange County. 
</P>
<P>
For details on the fairs, please see K28 
</P>
