<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHLAND'S TOP 10 BUILDING LEADERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Key to Home Builder Roster 
</P>
<P>
The name of each company is followed by its headquarters city and then by its 
principal officer. Sales figures are given for 1989, and have been limited to 
residential sales in Kern, Los Angeles, Orange, Riverside, San Bernardino, San 
Diego and Ventura counties. 
</P>
<P>
Sales projections are for anticipated residential sales in the above-mentioned 
counties for 1990. The number of units constructed in 1989 includes units 
completed for sale during 1989 and is broken out by number and percent of each 
type of unit: single-family homes, apartments and condominiums (including units 
in planned-unit developments). Inventory includes any units completed for sale 
that were unsold by the end of the accounting period. 
</P>
<P>
Note: Ranking is based on rounded sales figures. Subtotals may not add to 
100.0% due to computer rounding. Firms with the same 1989 sales volume are 
ranked in alphabetical order. 
</P>
<P>
* Firm reporting on a fiscal-year basis. 
</P>
<P>
The following builders changed their names in 1989: The Casden Co./CoastFed 
Properties from CoastFed Properties; Century Homes Communities from Century 
Homes; Forecast Group from Forecast Mortgage Corp.; Forest City Properties 
Corp. from Forest City Development; The Grupe Company from Grupe Development 
Co. -- Southern California; McKellar Communities from McKellar Development of 
La Jolla; McMillin Communities Inc. from McMillin Cos.; Meeker Development Co. 
from California Communities Inc.; Richmond American Homes from Richmond 
American; Socaland Group Inc. from Socaland Development or Socaland Corp.; 
Sunland Communities from Sunland Consolidated or The Sunland Housing Group. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
</P>
