<HEADLINE>
<P>
TOO BUSY FOR WORDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In regard to the March 8 edition of "48 Hours," I was depressed, maddened and 
confused to see those various episodes of people so busy, busy, busy. 
</P>
<P>
Get it done! Let's move in the fast lane! Gotta stay on the go-that's the name 
of the game in this day and age! All very efficient. 
</P>
<P>
So much so that their children are ignored. "Well, the kids have a busy 
schedule too." 
</P>
<P>
OK. But where and when does all this busy efficiency filter down to the common 
folk? Every time I call someone, I get a recording saying they're busy, "but 
we'll get right back to you" -- rarely is that the case. A letter mailed with 
an enclosed self-addressed, stamped envelope is seldom returned. I have an 
automobile accident (not my fault), and it takes weeks just for an insurance 
man to look at it. 
</P>
<P>
Just what is being done by these movers and shakers? 
</P>
<P>
William W. Campbell, Glendale 
</P>
</TEXT>
